arctica. The core, IODP Site 1333, is in the equatorial Pacific positioned far from either pole thus, a shift towards a less radiogenic Hf isotopic compositions is not to be expected. The absence of a shift in Hf isotopes in the oxydroxide leachates, or a shift of lesser magnitude, will strengthen the possibility of northern hemisphere glaciation.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85051", "section":"Paleoceanography and Paleoclimatology"} 
