hin the water column. Our 6-month water chemistry record reveals high concentrations of methane in the wet season, especially following rainfall events, and relatively lower methane concentrations in the dry season. These observations suggest rain flushes methane generated in overlying anoxic soils into the cave. DO, water level, and groundwater flow patterns were also linked to the precipitation record. These data provide novel insight into the interconnections between external climate forcing and subterranean anchialine ecosystems within coastal aquifers.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85439", "section":"Biogeosciences"} 
