2 highest biomass burning fluxes over Siberia during the simulation period 2010-2012. The biomass burning fluxes in Inv.GG were similar to a priori, but lower than Inv.GB (particularly in the eastern part of Siberia). In Inv.GG, the Jun-Aug biomass burning fluxes account for ~14% of the annual mean Siberian total flux in 2010-2012.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85487", "section":"Atmospheric Sciences"} 
