lifted backlimb surfaces preserve the deformed fan surface. The preliminary OSL results from alluvial fan units improve age control of previously defined surfaces, refining our understanding of the deposition and uplift of alluvial fan units on preserved on backlimb.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85604", "section":"Tectonophysics"} 
