eal nitrifiers occupy low-salinity and high-salinity niches, respectively. The nutrient concentrations and salinity might be the most important factors which are responsible for this niche diversification. Overall, this study shed light on our understanding of the biogeographic patterns and its ecological drivers of estuarine microbial communities.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85664", "section":"Biogeosciences"} 
