150 – 220 km. We also investigate the sensitivity of neutral and ion density retrievals to variability in solar irradiance, solar longitude, and local time. We compare our retrievals to predictions from the Mars Global Ionosphere-Thermosphere Model [MGITM, Bougher et al., 2015], as well as in situ measurements by the Neutral Gas Ionizing Mass Spectrometer [NGIMS, Mahaffy et al., 2014], and quantify the differences throughout the altitude region of interest. The N2/CO2 ratio is used to show that N2 is in the diffusively separated region of the Martian atmosphere with a mean mixing ratio that is consistent with model predictions from MGITM, as well as in situ measurements by Viking 1 & 2 [Nier and McElroy, 1977] and NGIMS.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85668", "section":"Planetary Sciences"} 
