bolism, and differences in the calculation of carbon flux anomalies based on method. The quantification of co-variation in these two methods of observation is important as it informs both how remotely sensed vegetation indices are correlated with on the ground tower observations, and with what certainty we can expand these observations and relationships.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85729", "section":"Biogeosciences"} 
