es to water quality. Our project aims to use this information in conjunction with data from the USGS SPARROW program to target non-point source hotspots of Nitrogen and Phosphorus addition and removal. By better understanding the flow dynamics within riparian areas during high flow events, riparian restoration projects can be carried out with improved efficacy.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/85791", "section":"Hydrology"} 
