nct from viral assemblages in other marine and terrestrial aquatic environments. Our data also suggest that viruses contribute to the mortality of deep subsurface prokaryotes through cell lysis, and viruses may alter the genetic potential of their hosts through the processes of lysogenic conversion and horizontal gene transfer.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86091", "section":"Biogeosciences"} 
