ents was present as Fe(II). One-third to one-half of the total biogenic Fe(II) extracted from sediments collected from a Montana prairie pothole located downgradient from a produced-water disposal pit was present as surface-complexed Fe(II).", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86272", "section":"Biogeosciences"} 
