{"authors":"Juan Martínez-Sykora::LMSAL--", "title":"Fourier Analysis Accelereated with GPUs on 3D Numerical Simulations of the Solar Atmosphere.", "abstract":"Solar dynamics from the convection zone create a variety of waves that may propagate through the solar atmosphere. These waves are important in facilitating the energy transfer between the sun’s surface and the corona as well as propagating energy throughout the solar system. How and where these waves are dissipated remains an open question. Advanced 3D Radiative-Magneticohydrodynamic numerical simulations have furthered our understanding of the processes involved. Fourier transformations analysis helps to understand the nature of the waves by finding the frequency and wavelength of these waves, as well as the nature of their propagation and where they get dissipated. In order to analyze the waves in the aforementioned simulations and models, Fast Fourier Transform algorithms will be applied. Since the processing of the Furier transform over the large 3D domains of the simulations would be time intensive and inefficient on a single processor (CPU), CUDA, a computing architecture that harnesses the power of the Graphycs Procesor Units (GPUs), will be used to accelerate the calculations.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86363", "section":""} 
