sitional effects are prevalent. Regions with higher anisotropy could be indicative of olivine-rich, strained mantle. However, lower anisotropy could be indicative of isotropic minerals such as eclogite. High Vp/Vs could suggest more garnet and pyroxene or a decrease in Mg. We will also calculate Sfast and Sslow wave differential attenuation, dt*, to evaluate regions where thermal or scattering effects dominate. ", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86438", "section":"Seismology"} 
