ncentration across temporal scales from daily rhythms to seasonal changes, during both baseflow and storm conditions. Discrete measurements of absorbance and fluorescence provided information about DOM composition throughout the study. Together these measurements give a detailed record of DOM dynamics in multiple perennial headwater streams for an entire year. This information could inform future studies, such as investigations into stream network scale thresholds in DOM cycling, carbon cycling modelling for the study region, or understanding the impact of wetlands sometimes considered geographically isolated on downstream ecosystems.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86441", "section":"Hydrology"} 
