ith image capture), making it easier to accommodate a variety of experiments. During each imaging session, integral metadata necessary for reproducing experiment results are collected (e.g., plant type and age, growing conditions and treatments, camera settings) using hierarchical data format files. These metadata are searchable within the GUI and can be selected and extracted for further analysis. The GUI also supports an image previewer that performs limited image processing (e.g., thresholding and cropping). Root skeletonization, 3D reconstruction and trait calculation (e.g., rooting depth, rooting angle, total volume of roots) is being developed in conjunction with this project.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86470", "section":"Hydrology"} 
