l item utility. As climate policy negotiations will consist of allocation of scarce resources and rejection of certain attributes, a conjoint analysis is an ideal tool for evaluating policy outcomes. This research program seeks to provide a commentary useful to policy makers on the most desirable outcomes of the negotiations and other international cooperation.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86682", "section":"Public Affairs"} 
