LOC (Scanning Habitable Environments with Raman & Luminescence). The geologic story as told by the Mars 2020 instrument data will be analyzed and compared to the full suite of data collected by hyperspectral imaging and terrestrial techniques (e.g. XRD) applied to the collected hand samples. This work will shed light on the potential uses and synergies of the Mars 2020 instrument suite, especially with regards to spectral (i.e. remote) recognition of important and interesting samples on which to do contact science.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/86694", "section":"Planetary Sciences"} 
