{"authors":"Mauricio Fuentes::University of Chile--", "title":"S54C-03: A study of the 2015 Mw 8.3 Illapel Earthquake and tsunami: Numerical and Analytical approaches.", "abstract":"The recent Illapel Earthquake triggered a large tsunami causing economic losses and fatalities. In order to study the coastal effects, different finite fault models are used to define the initial condition for the tsunami simulation. The numerical code NEOWAVE is employed to obtain the tsunami evolution through the Pacific Ocean. Taking attention into the short time response, because the earthquake and tsunami sources are close to the coast, understanding of the near field run-up behavior is highly relevant for Chile. Therefore, an analytical solution of the 2+1 D shallow water wave equations is considered. With this solution, we estimate the run-up distribution, at first order, along the coastline. Field observations were measured in the surrounded coastal area of the earthquake, where the tsunami took place with higher penetration. We compare between the analytical and numerical solutions, to test how accurate is the method from the analytical point of view. Then, we compare both with field run-up measurements. We observe consistency between both approaches. To complete the analysis, a tsunami source inversion is performed using run-up field measurements, DART buoys and coastal tide gauges, then, the inversion is compared with the used seismic model.", "url":"https://agu.confex.com/agu/fm15/meetingapp.cgi/Paper/93959", "section":"Seismology"} 
